ttp://pub30.ezboard.com/usenidyen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senidyen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/01 1:07:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub30.ezboard.com/fthesentinentfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ranger information</span><hr size=1> Hello everyone,<br><br>Shoumai and I have been having a ball with our leezard monks.  The downside is that I have more free time and lvl faster than he does <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Sooo, I decided to start another character that I can play when he needs to catch up a lvl or so, and went with the ranger.<br><br>My ranger is a Half Elf(I cant stand the wood elf town) around the Qeynos.  I know that we have a lot of rangers in the guild so I thought I would ask some questions of you guys.  I have never played a ranger so i could use a little help.<br><br>1)  right now I have some banded peices off of my shaman, what would be the next step after banded...ivy?<br><br>2)  what weapons are good for a ranger.  I am going for dual weild.  I am still using my newbie sword until I can save some money for a better weapon.  I thought about going for a Velium Scimitar.<br><br>3)  What are some good quest for a ranger.  I am only lvl 4 right now so I know selection will be slim.  But do any of you have a quest you really liked bellow 20 that might be a good one for me to try.<br><br>Thanks in advance for your advise,<br><br>Senidyen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ualzabomachera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alzabo Machera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Member</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/01 12:24:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub30.ezboard.com/fthesentinentfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ranger information</span><hr size=1> I can help.IMHO,2h slash is great until you get the ability to duel weild/double attack.After that make it a priority to get weapons that have low delay any thing under 25d should be good.I found I could solo Alazabo till almost 20.Just be careful.Before you shell out a bunch cash for weapons,I've got a few things you can have.Nothing Uber but good starting stuff for a newbie.As for armor,Banded is the armor you will have too use there are some oddball bits and pieces of armor you can pick up here and there,like mino ribcage,turtle shell helm,etc.Personally I would stick with the banded,save your money for the Ivy(you need 300pp to buy the rubies for the Ivy BP quest)I'm in Kunark now but I can get over to see you this weekend.Need to get my Hide skill any ways.I can also buy my Level 30 spells while im there.Gimme a shout when your in game I'll get a port and head over.Lata <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ualzabomachera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alzabo Machera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Member</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/01 12:38:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub30.ezboard.com/fthesentinentfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ranger information</span><hr size=1> One more thing,As soon as you get your forage skill set a hot key for it.You save so much cash not having to buy food and water. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/bthesentinent.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ilrissa>Ilrissa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Officer</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/01 1:34:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub30.ezboard.com/fthesentinentfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ranger information</span><hr size=1> Ah Rangers my favorite subject. Weapons A Bow and a Long sword. I think I have a Combine in bank still. Get yourself a fletching kit. If you desire I can teach you how to make arrows and eventually bows. Banded Armor is the best without doing the Ivy quest.<br> <br>1)Do the Mail run from Sure fall to Qeynos <br>2)The broken arrows from Guard weleth in N.Qeynos to Nestiff in S.Qeynos.<br>3)On the way to Qeynos hunt Rabid wolves and turn the pelts in to Temple in Qeynos (priestess Caulria)<br>4)Kill all the gnolls you can see.<br>5)Repeat often<br><br>Use your bow as much as possible youll hate later levels when you get a good bow and cant hit poop. I have always used 1HS never put much stock into 2HS. When you have dual wield and double attack plus kick it works just as well.<br><br>Practice forage and swimming. At about 9th lvl you can go behind the waterfall in Sure Fall and hunt poachers. Be careful Con first. I do this while I'm fletching or swimming. Make track one of your hot buttons and use all the time (this is your biggest skill) <br><br>Hopefully you will find this useful. Oh BTW if you are killing bears or wolves in Q Hills stay away from Holly!!!!<br><br>Ilrissa Silverhand<br>Elmarra Silverhand<br>Queshu  <br>Radina<br>&lt;Too many more to list&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ualzabomachera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alzabo Machera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Member</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/01 2:21:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub30.ezboard.com/fthesentinentfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ranger information</span><hr size=1> Also Buy a fletch kit as soon as you can.I recomended 2hs because at the time I started mt ranger,there was very little available to me for decent 1 handers.Just my opinion,but 1hs is going to be the best,and most useful skill when you get the abilities of deul weild and double attack.But until then as far as dealing out some decent damage I found 2 handers to be my choice.Good Luck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/bthesentinent.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sentry>Sentry</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Officer</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/01 3:21:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub30.ezboard.com/fthesentinentfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ranger information</span><hr size=1> All good advice.  As to spells, when Dance of the Fireflies is available (15) get it and practice it.  It makes no sense to actually use it as a half-elf but it gets conjuration up, and you want this big-time at 30.  Never found a use for Lull Animal (9).  Don't underestimate Flame Lick early on.  Glimpse (9) also has its uses.  Snare (9), as they say, is God-like.  Camouflage (15) only slightly less so.  Harmony (22) is like Camo.<br><br>IMO keep All your combat skills up, except Hand-to-Hand, which caps too low to be useful except when you should be dead anyway.  If you practice 2h skills early you'll be able to use the occasional cool weapon your mates can't.  1h skills (slash, blunt and piercing) go up real well once you get dual wield, but 2h slash and blunt take work.  Do it while you can still get exp for it.<br><br>Get a fletching kit in Surefall and learn to make your own arrows -- better and cheaper.  Don't bother with Throw, do Archery.  Practice Sense Heading a lot and finding locs, minimizing the 'Lost Ranger' cracks.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ucaederedraconis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caedere Draconis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/01 4:21:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub30.ezboard.com/fthesentinentfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.thesentinent.com/redmage.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ranger information</span><hr size=1> Good info on the spells, Sentry!<br><br>As he said, PRACTICE YOUR CONJURATION!  I can't emphasize that enough!  At level 30, your two most damaging spells are Cancel Magic ('cause you can remove HP buffs from the mobs, sharply dropping their HP for a low mana cost), and Stinging Swarm.  SS will eat your mana, half your food, most of what you have in the bank, and lower your gas mileage if you don't have your conjuration maxed when you get the spell.  Well, at least it'll eat your mana.<br><br>Also, use Glimpse to practice Divination early-on 'cause when you get Camo, you'll be sorry if you're caught in a fizzle-storm while trying to do some emergency invis'ing.<br><br>Practice *all* of your melee weapon skills.  Why?  Well, there are kick-ass weapons from each type, and it's a MAJOR pain trying to get your piercing skill from 5 to 170 when you're level 33  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  When you max one skill, switch weapons, and keep doing that throughout each level.  I can't emphasize enough how much I wish I'd done that.<br><br>Get your fletching to 101 if you plan on keeping your ranger.  You'll need a skill of 101 or higher to keep your 1/150 arrows affordable.  You'll only have about a 5-7% failure rate at that level.<br><br>Never underestimate the importance of agility.  They can't damage what they can't hit.  As a ranger, expect to be hit *hard* when they actually get a decent hit on you.<br><br>You can now swing immediately after casting a spell.  You can also cast immediately after shooting an arrow, and vice-versa.  Snare and Grasping Roots now stack.  Take advantage of these.  Snare, shoot, root, shoot, nuke, shoot, nuke, shoot, etc.  <br><br>Also, when meleeing, don't be afraid to toss in some nukes to raise your damage output, as long as the cast time is worth it.  (You don't wanna cast a 37-point damage nuke if a long cast time would keep you from landing two or three 19 or 25-point hits.)  Likewise, if you're having a crappy time hitting something that isn't fire-resistant, maybe those nukes are worth the time after all  =).<br><br>That's about all I can think of at the moment  =). <p><b>Caedere Draconis, "Ranjuh Pet" Protégé of 33 Tall Tales</b><br><FONT Size=1>"A Native American elder once described his own inner struggles in this manner: 'Inside of me there are two dogs. One of the dogs is mean and evil. The other dog is good. The mean dog fights the good dog all the time.' When asked which dog wins, he reflected for a moment and replied, 'The one I feed the most.' " (George Bernard Shaw)</FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/usenidyen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senidyen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/01 11:44:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub30.ezboard.com/fthesentinentfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ranger information</span><hr size=1> Thanks for all of the information guys.  At lvl 4 my defense is nearly maxed.  I think my agi is 95-100.  Not sure.  Thanks Alzabo for offering me some weapons.  I will look for you the next time I am on.<br><br>Thanks guys for all of the replies.  They help a lot.  <br><br>Hope to see you in game!<br>Senidyen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/bthesentinent.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sentry>Sentry</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Officer</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#333333>(2/3/01 3:13:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub30.ezboard.com/fthesentinentfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ranger information</span><hr size=1> Thanks, Caedere.  It never occurred to me to cast Cancel on a monster if it didn't have a damage shield up.  They're buffed?  Have to try that.<br><br>And I think 70 skill in fletching would suffice to get 1/150s to as good as they get (95% success rate).  They triv at 56, according to Aoenla's guide<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~ewj/fletchguide/index.htm,">members.bellatlantic.net/...index.htm,</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> and my own studies suggest that when things triv, they work 80% of the time.  Skill points above and below that add or subtract 1% each.  Things never get worse than 5% or better than 95%.  And yes wisdom or intelligence or phases of the moon make some difference too.<br><br>Sentry<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/usenidyen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senidyen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#333333>(2/5/01 11:44:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub30.ezboard.com/fthesentinentfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ranger Update!</span><hr size=1> My ranger is now lvl 9.  I gave him some weapons off my warrior so I should be fine there for now.  Thanks for the offers of help.<br><br>My fletching is now 36!  Made myself a bow...which was cool.<br><br>Got one more question.  Is there a trick to raising sense heading?  I have been cranking that button like crazy for 4 lvls or so and my skill is only 8!.  And is there a quicker way to raise archery?  I put some points into it and I use it to pull.  If in a group, I will back away from a fight towards the end to try to get it up more, but it hasnt gone up any after putting the points in.  Is there another trick i can try on raising my archery skill?<br><br>Thanks oh wise rangers<br>Senidyen<br><br>P.S.  My ranger's name is Duadien.  I am currently in Qeynos area so if you need help with something...send me a tell. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/usenidyen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senidyen</A> at: 2/5/01 11:47:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/bthesentinent.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ilrissa>Ilrissa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Officer</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/01 8:36:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub30.ezboard.com/fthesentinentfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ranger Update!</span><hr size=1> Sense Heading: No really fast ways there. Try going across West Karana a couple of times I think thats How I got Elmarras up so high.<br><br>Archery: Best tactic now that you have snare is<br><br>1. Find large open area where not too many MOBs  will agro on you just for being there.<br><br>2. Cast Snare on your Target<br><br>3. Three Run backwards while still facing your target.<br><br>4. Fire your bow while still running backwards.<br><br>5. You should be able to get off about 2 or 3 arrows before melee<br><br>Try this out on greenies until you get the hang of it. Even at 26 my archery isnt that great but its worth it when you see that crit hit message come up. <br><br>Goodluck<br><br>Ilrissa Silverhand<br>Elmarra Silverhand<br>Queshu<br>Radina<br>&lt;too many to list here&gt;  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ucaederedraconis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caedere Draconis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/01 2:38:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub30.ezboard.com/fthesentinentfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.thesentinent.com/redmage.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ranger Update!</span><hr size=1> Yeah, it's gonna take alot of arrows to raise the skill.  Mine's at about 170 right now, though, and well worth it.  I usually hit for 28 with 1 dmg arrows and a 20 dmg bow--not a bad little damage bonus!  The crits for 44-59 are nice, too.<br><br>Like Ilrissa said, just bow-kite things around.  Once you get the hang of kiting greenies, try something bigger 'cause you sure ain't gonna raise your skill on them.  Also, if you see someone killing a HG or something, ask them to let